</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dorsum of head with minute punctures, clypeus smooth, with strong luster (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7E</figureCitation>
). Clypeus elevated, anterior margin roundly incised; labrum as long as broad, apex round; malar space 1.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of middle ocellus; postocellar area 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long, middle furrow weak; lateral furrows distinct, feebly divergent backwards; POL: OOL: OCL = 3: 5: 6; head behind eyes weakly enlarged (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7C</figureCitation>
). Antenna 1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
head breadth, club breadth 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
apical breadth of antennomere 3, club length 1.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as antennomere 3 and 1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
combined length of antennomeres 4 and 5 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7D</figureCitation>
), antennomere 3 as long as longest axis of eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Mesonotum minutely and densely punctured (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7B</figureCitation>
); scutellum roundly elevated without middle furrow, dorsum densely punctured; mesepisternum above carina densely and minutely punctured mixed with microsculptures, oblique carina on mesopleuron sharp, mesepimeron largely polished, shiny (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7F</figureCitation>
); cenchri very narrow and about 4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, distance between inner margin of cenchri 2.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longest axis of a cenchrus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Abdomen</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Abdominal tergum 1 minutely punctured mixed with microsculptures, without lateral smooth patch; lateral carina low and obtuse, anterior and posterior corners round, posterior margin with broad and deep incision, bottom round (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7G</figureCitation>
); middle process of sternum 7 broad and triangular, basal breadth about 1/3 breadth of sternite 7; lance long and slender, subapical annuli clearly broadened, total length of annuli 5.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
height of 13th annulus, first annulus 1.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7L</figureCitation>
); lancet with 57 annuli and 56 serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7L</figureCitation>
), middle serrulae weakly narrowed toward truncate apex, each side with 4-5 large subbasal teeth, distance between middle serrulae 2.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
basal breadth of serrulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Asicimbex koreanus Yan &amp; Wei sp. nov., holotype, female A female adult in dorsal view B thoracic notum C head in dorsal view D antenna E head in front view F mesopleuron and metapleuron G abdominal terga H lateral side of abdomen I ovipositor sheath in ventral view J tibia and tarsus K claw L lancet M middle serrulae." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.83710.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707230" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">7M</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="265">Male.</emphasis>
Color and structure similar to female. Genitalia not examined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
